On Mon, 26 Apr 2004, Frank E Biffath III wrote:

> You have to love the karma of the VW.  Hapybus took me on a 1300 mile round
> trip to EveryBus with nary a problem.  Back at home, first ride, and it leaves
> me needing assistance.
> Out of no where, I have zero juice to the key.
> I can connect jumper cables, and it starts.  Remove the cables and you can
> hear the power drop.
> My conclusions, with Bentley help.... alternator or (now I cant even
> remember)
> Bentley wasn't real clear, seemed to be more for the generator on a 1600.
> This is a 78 FI.

personally I would disconect and charge the battery, then do the battery
drain circuit testing until I found the reason the battery was going flat,
if  it is the Volt reg or alt it would be also shown, but I suspect first
you may have a short or crossed circuit that is draining the juice.

Bob

